go for one's/your life
Homonym Number:
Word Class: phrase
Sense Number:
Definition:to begin or do something vigorously; to run away quickly. (He was caught in the orchard and went for his life.
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
